## 9. Scraper Architecture

### Active Sources
| Source | Method | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Controller.com | Playwright + Chrome extension (Distil bypass) | Challenge-gated; use extension |
| Trade-A-Plane | DataDome cookie session + adaptive rate | `adaptive_rate.py` |
| AvBuyer | requests + Playwright fallback | `--new-only` monitor mode |
| AeroTrader | requests + BeautifulSoup | |
| AircraftForSale (AFS) | requests | |
| ASO | Playwright (ASP.NET paging) | Deep scrape with slow pacing |
| GlobalAir | requests + Playwright | Category-scoped, Searchanise avionics |
| Barnstormers | requests + BeautifulSoup | No significant bot protection |

### Scraper Rules
- Always import from `scraper_base.py` for rate limiting and upsert — don't reinvent
- All output must conform to the canonical schema in `scraper/schema.py`
- `source` + `source_id` is the upsert conflict key for all scrapers
- Unknown payload keys → fold into `raw_data.bridge_unmapped`, never block upserts
- Rate limiting: `random.uniform(N, M)` seconds between requests — be respectful
- Fingerprinting: hash title+price+description[:200] to skip unchanged detail re-fetches
- Checkpoint files in `scraper/state/` — all long-running scrapers must support `--resume`
- FAA non-US registrations: guard enrichment for non-US N-numbers (don't attempt FAA lookup on foreign tails)

