## 12. Code Quality Standards

### TypeScript / Next.js
- No ad-hoc Supabase queries in route files — use `listingsRepository.ts`
- Dynamic imports with `{ ssr: false }` for any component using D3, Three.js, or browser APIs
- ISR: `export const revalidate = 120` on public listing pages; `unstable_cache` 90s for filter options
- Error handling: never let a single API failure crash a page — fail soft with graceful degradation
- `count: planned` (planner estimate) instead of `count: exact` for filtered listing counts
- Parallel data fetching with `Promise.all` for independent queries

### Python
- Schema validation on all scraper write paths
- Sanitize `engine_model`/`faa_engine_model` before any scoring write
- Use `_build_engine_lookup_candidates()` for engine token extraction — don't write new regex
- Parser-derived values must be coerced to integer-safe types before DB writes (no float engine hours)
- Always emit `extractor_version` / `intelligence_version` fields on write

### Migrations
- Sequential naming: `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`
- Always additive — never drop or rename columns in a single migration (add new, deprecate old)
- Update `public_listings` view in the same migration that adds new scoring columns
- After any migration touching `public_listings`, update `PUBLIC_LISTINGS_VIEW.md`

